dataIdInfo.idPurp: California Elections Code § 21500 requires the County Board of Supervisors to adjust the Supervisorial district boundaries every ten years following the federal Census so that the districts are as "nearly equal in population as may be" and comply with the Voting Rights Act. 2011, the Board of Supervisors is required to redistrict the five Supervisorial districts using 2010 Census data. The County’s redistricting process included broad opportunity for public review and input. The Board adopted the redistricting ordinance on September 27, 2011.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Five (5) supervisoral districts of San Diego County
